          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Schema Design for RAG Content"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) system retrieves text chunks from a knowledge base and injects them into the LLM prompt as context. The schema backing that knowledge base must balance three competing concerns: fast vector similarity search, flexible metadata filtering for multi-tenant isolation, and an audit trail of which chunks were retrieved for which user messages."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This sub-subtopic presents a production-ready PostgreSQL schema for RAG content, explains the reasoning behind each design choice, and shows the Python code that inserts and queries it."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "RAG content schema: sources \u2192 documents \u2192 chunks, plus retrieval_log junction table and key indexes"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Four-Table Design"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The schema has four tables with a clear hierarchy:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "sources",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 tracks the origin of each document (a URL, an S3 path, an uploaded file). Deduplication on "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "url + checksum",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " prevents re-ingesting unchanged content."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "documents",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 one row per logical document (a PDF page range, a Markdown file, a web article). Carries language, total token count, and a JSON metadata bag for arbitrary per-document attributes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
